<paragraph blockId="18.[178,1085,495,546]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835">
Female. 
<typeStatus box="[267,365,495,517]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835">Holotype</typeStatus>
. Figs 68-69. Measurements: body length = 
<quantity box="[822,885,495,517]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835" unit="mm" value="9.0">9 mm</quantity>
; forewing length = 
<quantity box="[178,258,524,546]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[178,1085,562,789]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835">
Black, brown, bright ferruginous. Wings light yellow. Brown: clypeus, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[933,972,562,584]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835">Tsa</emphasis>
, antennae, mandibles.Bright ferruginous are veins and pterostigma, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[754,814,591,615]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835">
LaSt 
<subScript attach="left" box="[806,814,601,615]" fontSize="6" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
, legs but coxae, the whole of metasoma. Light brownish spurs, spines and hair throughout. Head strongly transversal in frontal aspect: ratio 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[456,491,650,672]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835">LA</emphasis>
/ 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[498,516,650,672]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835">A</emphasis>
~ 1.25. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[609,657,650,672]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835">PoG</emphasis>
not expressed, base of hypostoma semitransparent and swollen, breaking 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[545,587,679,701]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835">cOc</emphasis>
which is not complete. Large semitransparent apical border of 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[360,386,708,732]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835">
N 
<subScript attach="both" box="[378,386,718,732]" fontSize="6" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
disk. Fine wrinkles along sides of the horizontal area and strong waving wrinkles on the declivitous area of 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[622,636,737,759]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835">P</emphasis>
. Gradulus of 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[791,807,731,745]" fontSize="6" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835">nd</superScript>
tergum well arched. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1026,1040,737,759]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835">p</emphasis>
like the standard of the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[178,349,804,826]" box="[178,349,804,826]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835">Male. Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[178,382,841,863]" box="[178,382,841,863]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835">Ecology. Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[178,888,878,900]" box="[178,888,878,900]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1835">Derivatio nominis. From the Greek διαπυρος = bright red and γαστηρ.</paragraph>
